Comparisons : Much/A lot/Lots/A Bit/A Little

We use very to modify adjectives and adverbs, but we do not use very to modify comparative adjectives and adverbs.

He is ver old.

NOT : He is very older than me.

Instead, we use much/a lot/lots/a bit/a little to change the strength of the comparison. 
Note that some of these are more informal than others.

Formal
She's much older than me.

The new boss's much friendlier than the last boss.

It's a little less expensive than the other one.

Informal
He's a lot taller than me.

She looks lots more comfortable today.

It was a bit cheaper than the gold one.
